Troubleshooting Tips
Issue: Data generation produces unrealistic values

Solution: Verify baseline metrics are reasonable (phishing: 10-20%, incidents: 5-10/month)
Check improvement factors use gradual curves, not linear progression
Ensure costs include both fixed (setup) and variable (operational) components
Issue: ROI calculations show negative values throughout

Solution: Review benefit calculations - ensure all three categories are included (incident savings, productivity, compliance)
Verify incident cost per event is realistic ($20,000-$30,000)
Check that improvement factors are applied correctly to baseline metrics
Issue: Visualizations don't display or show errors

Solution: Ensure matplotlib backend is configured: export MPLBACKEND=Agg for headless environments
Verify all required columns exist in DataFrame before plotting
Check file paths are correct and directories exist
Issue: Dashboard won't start

Solution: Verify port 8050 is available: netstat -tuln | grep 8050
Check Dash and Plotly are installed: pip list | grep -E "dash|plotly"
Run with debug mode: app.run_server(debug=True) to see detailed errors
